   {{b_1}}  \cr 
   {{b_2}}  \cr 
   {{b_3}}  \cr 

 } } \right]$$ such that $${b_1},{b_2},{b_3} \in R$$ and the system of equations (in real variables)<br><br>$$\eqalign{
  &amp;  - x + 2y + 5z = {b_1}  \cr 
  &amp; 2x - 4y + 3z = {b_2}  \cr 
  &amp; x - 2y + 2z = {b_3} \cr} $$<br><br>has at least one solution. Then, which of the following system(s) (in real variables) has (have) at least one solution for each $$\left[ {\matrix{
   {{b_1}}  \cr 
   {{b_2}}  \cr 
   {{b_3}}  \cr 

 } } \right]$$$$ \in $$S?

