 } } \right|$$<br><br>$$ = 1(0 - 12) - 2( - 10 - 3) + 5(8 - 0) = 54$$<br><br>$$D \ne 0$$<br><br>$$ \therefore $$ It has unique solutino for any b<sub>1</sub>, b<sub>2</sub>, b<sub>3</sub>.

We have, <br><br>Equations of circle<br><br>$${x^2} + {y^2} = {1 \over 2}$$<br><br>and Equations of parabola<br><br>y<sup>2</sup> = 4x<br><br> <img src="https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1kywtgr6r/28e8b480-f65e-4214-a2e7-8d2d8a289cc5/7eace640-7f59-11ec-91f0-35ffd68c9c48/file-1kywtgr6s.png?format=png" data-orsrc="https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1kywtgr6r/28e8b480-f65e-4214-a2e7-8d2d8a289cc5/7eace640-7f59-11ec-91f0-35ffd68c9c48/file-1kywtgr6s.png" loading="lazy" style="max-width: 100%;height: auto;display: block;margin: 0 auto;max-height: 60vh" alt="JEE Advanced 2018 Paper 2 Offline Mathematics - Conic Sections Question 18 English Explanation 1"> <br><br>Let the equation of common tangent of parabola and circle is<br><br>$$y = mx + {1 \over m}$$<br><br>Since, radius of circle = $${1 \over {\sqrt 2 }}$$<br><br>$$ \therefore $$ $${1 \over {\sqrt 2 }}$$ = $$\left| {{{0 + 0 + {1 \over m}} \over {\sqrt {1 + {m^2}} }}} \right|$$<br><br>$$ \Rightarrow $$ m<sup>4</sup> + m<sup>2</sup> $$-$$ 2 = 0<br><br>$$ \Rightarrow $$ m =$$ \pm $$1<br><br>$$ \therefore $$ Equation of common tangents are<br><br>y = x + 1 and y = $$-$$x$$-$$1<br><br>Intersection  point of common tangent at Q($$-$$1, 0)<br><br>$$ \therefore $$ Equation of ellipse<br><br>$${{{x^2}} \over 1} + {{{y^2}} \over {1/2}} = 1$$<br><br>where, $${a^2} = 1$$, $${b^2} = 1/2$$<br><br>Now, eccentricity<br><br>$$ = \sqrt {1 - {{{b^2}} \over {{a^2}}}}  = \sqrt {1 - {1 \over 2}}  = {1 \over {\sqrt 2 }}$$<br><br>and length of latusrectum<br><br>$$ = {{2{b^2}} \over a} = {{2\left( {{1 \over 2}} \right)} \over 1} = 1$$<br><br> <img src="https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1kywtjuno/7f360897-d3f6-47ac-8152-d0643da44ca6/d4c85b40-7f59-11ec-91f0-35ffd68c9c48/file-1kywtjunp.png?format=png" data-orsrc="https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1kywtjuno/7f360897-d3f6-47ac-8152-d0643da44ca6/d4c85b40-7f59-11ec-91f0-35ffd68c9c48/file-1kywtjunp.png" loading="lazy" style="max-width: 100%;height: auto;display: block;margin: 0 auto;max-height: 60vh" alt="JEE Advanced 2018 Paper 2 Offline Mathematics - Conic Sections Question 18 English Explanation 2"><br><br>$$ \therefore $$ Area of shaded region<br><br>$$ = 2\int_{1/\sqrt 2 }^1 {{1 \over {\sqrt 2 }}} \sqrt {1 - {x^2}} dx$$<br><br>$$\eqalign{
  &amp;  = \sqrt 2 \left[ {{x \over 2}\sqrt {1 - {x^2}}  + {1 \over 2}{{\sin }^{ - 1}}x} \right]_{1/\sqrt 2 }^1  \cr 
  &amp;  = \sqrt 2 \left[ {\left( {0 + {\pi  \over 4}} \right) - \left( {{1 \over 4} + {\pi  \over 8}} \right)} \right] \cr} $$<br><br>$$ = \sqrt 2 \left[ {\left( {0 + {\pi  \over 4}} \right) - \left( {{1 \over 4} + {\pi  \over 8}} \right)} \right]$$<br><br>$$ = \sqrt 2 \left( {{\pi  \over 8} - {1 \over 4}} \right) = {{\pi  - 2} \over {4\sqrt 2 }}$$

Let $$Det(P) = \left| {\matrix{
