t] \cup \left[ {{e \over {e - 1}},\,\infty } \right)$$<br><br>and Range of $${x \over {x - 1}}$$ is R<sup>+</sup> $$-$$ {1}<br><br>$$ \Rightarrow $$ Range of f is R $$-$$ {0} or ($$-$$$$\infty $$, 0) $$ \cup $$ (0, $$\infty $$)<br><br>Range of g is $$\left[ { - {\pi  \over 2},{\pi  \over 2}} \right] - \{ 0\} $$ or $$\left[ { - {\pi  \over 2},0} \right) \cup \left( {0,{\pi  \over 2}} \right]$$<br><br>Now, P $$ \to $$ 4, Q $$ \to $$ 2, R $$ \to $$ 1, S $$ \to $$ 1<br><br>Hence, option (a) is correct answer.

